               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17590912-33-off192-c237" targOrder="Y" targets="t17590912-33-defend301 t17590912-33-off192 t17590912-33-verdict196"></join>
         
               <p>280. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17590912-33-defend301" type="defendantName">
                     Richard 
                     Outwood 
                  <interp inst="t17590912-33-defend301" type="surname" value="Outwood"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590912-33-defend301" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590912-33-defend301" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17590912-33-off192" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17590912-33-off192" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590912-33-off192" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing eight hats, value 10 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17590912-33-victim303" type="victimName">
                     Richard 
                     Fillison 
                  <interp inst="t17590912-33-victim303" type="surname" value="Fillison"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590912-33-victim303" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590912-33-victim303" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17590912-33-off192 t17590912-33-victim303"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17590912-33-cd193" type="crimeDate">Sept. 7</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17590912-33-off192 t17590912-33-cd193"></join>. ++.</p>
               <p>The prosecutor is a <rs id="t17590912-33-viclabel194" type="occupation">Hatter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17590912-33-victim303 t17590912-33-viclabel194"></join> in <placeName id="t17590912-33-crimeloc195">the Haymarket</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17590912-33-crimeloc195" type="placeName" value="the Haymarket"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17590912-33-crimeloc195" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17590912-33-off192 t17590912-33-crimeloc195"></join>; he lost eight hats on the 7th of September out of his shop; and 
               <persName id="t17590912-33-person304">
                  John 
                  Pamperton 
               <interp inst="t17590912-33-person304" type="surname" value="Pamperton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590912-33-person304" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590912-33-person304" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             a Watchman in St Ann's parish stopped the prisoner in the street with them under his arm, by which means they came to the knowledge of the prosecutor. The hats produced and deposed to.</p>
               <p>The prisoner in his defence, said two lads gave the hats to him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17590912-33-verdict196" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17590912-33-verdict196" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17590912-33-punish197" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17590912-33-punish197" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17590912-33-defend301 t17590912-33-punish197"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
